<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND BOX OFFICE; 'GUMP' IS KING OF THE YEAR--FOR NOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID J. FOX 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The weekend's moviegoing pushed Paramount Pictures' "Forrest Gump" past Walt 
Disney Pictures' "The Lion King" to make it the year's biggest box-office hit. 
"Gump," starring Tom Hanks, has thus far grossed $269.7 million, to the 
"King's" $267 million.However, the Disney animated movie will come back to 
theaters during the holiday season and is expected to regain the lead. The 
"Gump" total also makes it the fifth highest-grossing domestic release in 
history. 
</P>
