<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: FRANKFURT; OLD FAIR, NEW MEDIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The 46th Frankfurt Bookfair opens today with special emphasis on the world of 
multimedia and on Brazilian literature. 
</P>
<P>
 The new media -- electronic books, CD-ROM and videos -- made their debut at 
Frankfurt, the world's largest book fair, last year and will account for about 
220 of the 8,600 exhibits this week. 
</P>
<P>
 However, fair Director Peter Weidhass hastens to say that "with all the 
euphoria around the new media, the book will not lose its importance." 
Scheduled is a "Meeting With Culture" segment from Brazil, with 60 Brazilian 
authors leading discussions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
