<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS : VENTURA; 2 ARRESTED AFTER MAN SHOT IN HAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura man was shot in the hand early Monday after he was kidnaped and 
taken to a remote orchard outside Fillmore, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Shaun A. Landy, 29, was shot about 4 a.m. at Sycamore Road and Young Street, 
deputies said.He fled into an orange grove and had a nearby resident call for 
help. 
</P>
<P>
 Shortly thereafter, sheriff's deputies arrested Raymond S. Price, 36, and his 
girlfriend, Cathy E. Jordan, 28, both of Ventura, on suspicion of attempted 
murder and kidnaping, Ventura police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Landy told police he had gone to Price's house in the 1500 block of Nevin 
Avenue in Ventura to settle a dispute about some construction tools that Landy 
had borrowed, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 An argument ensued, during which Landy said he was beaten up, ordered into a 
truck and taken to the orchard, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Price and Jordan were being held at Ventura County Jail in lieu of $250,000 
bail each, Sheriff's Sgt. Jeff Matson said. Both are scheduled to be arraigned 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Landy was taken to Santa Paula Memorial Hospital, where a spokeswoman said he 
was treated for a gunshot wound to the left hand and then released. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
