<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS : OJAI; THREE AREA LIBRARIES SEEKING VOLUNTEERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Public libraries in Ojai, Meiners Oaks and Oak View are seeking volunteers to 
help shelve books and refurbish well-worn covers. 
</P>
<P>
 Volunteers must be able to file numerically and alphabetically, and are asked 
to work two to four hours a week for 12 weeks.Volunteers also must be able to 
pull a book cart. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone interested in learning more about public libraries and helping to 
maintain book collections should call Trish Cavanaugh, community relations 
manager with the county Library Services Agency, at 652-7517. 
</P>
<P>
 Prospective volunteers may also visit their local library and speak with the 
volunteer supervisor. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ojai Library is at 111 E. Ojai Ave., and is open from 10 a.m. to 9 p.m. 
Mondays, Tuesdays and Wednesdays; from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Thursdays, and from 
noon to 5 p.m. Saturdays. 
</P>
<P>
 The Meiners Oaks Library, at 114 N. Padre Juan Ave., is open from 10 a.m. to 6 
p.m. Mondays, and from 2 to 6 p.m. Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Hours at the Oak View Library, at 469 N. Ventura Ave., are from 2 to 6 p.m. 
Mondays, from 10 a.m. to 1 p.m. and 2 to 6 p.m. Tuesdays, and 2 to 6 p.m. 
Wednesdays and Thursdays. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
