<TEXT>
<P>
 A Colorado man who stopped in Fillmore with car trouble found himself behind 
bars after Ventura County sheriff's deputies discovered about $53,000 worth of 
cocaine in his vehicle, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Salvador Valadezcruz, 35, of Colorado Springs was arrested at 11:58 p.m. 
Sunday at Ventura and Saratoga streets, where he had pulled over because of car 
trouble, narcotics Detective Mike Horne said. 
</P>
