<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: 51 IN COUNTY NAMED MERIT SEMIFINALISTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DESIREE DREEUWS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fifty-one students attending schools in the Ventura County area have been 
named semifinalists in the National Merit Scholarship Program. 
</P>
<P>
 The semifinalists are eligible to win one of 6,700 Merit Scholarships, worth 
$26 million, to be awarded next spring, contest organizers said. 
</P>
<P>
 More than a million juniors nationwide entered the competition, but just 
15,000 semifinalists were chosen, officials said. The students entered the 
contest by scoring high academically on a screening test. 
</P>
<P>
 About 90% of the semifinalists are expected to become finalists, officials 
said. 
</P>
