<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEARCHERS LOOK FOR MISSING HIKER, 15 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 15-year-old Thousand Oaks girl has been missing since she went hiking alone 
Sunday, authorities said. Her disappearance sparked a search Monday evening by 
the Ventura County sheriff's search and rescue unit. 
</P>
<P>
 Lennea Diederichs went hiking in the rugged 1,700-acre Wildwood Park in 
Thousand Oaks at about 3 p.m. Sunday wearing only a shirt, shorts and shoes, 
Sheriff's Sgt. Robert Sparks said. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl's parents reported her missing shortly after 5 p.m. Monday, Sparks 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 At 6:55 p.m., shortly after sundown, a sheriff's helicopter and a team of 15 
volunteers from the East County search and rescue team descended on the park to 
search for the missing teen-ager. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl's parents, Dorn and Connie Diederichs, told police that the girl, a 
student at Conejo Valley High School, is very familiar with the park's hiking 
paths, Sparks said. The Diederichs were at the park Monday evening helping the 
search and rescue team decide where to look. 
</P>
