<HEADLINE>
<P>
TITANS' BROWN OUT FOR SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton soccer player Demian Brown will be out the rest of the 
season because of a torn anterior cruciate ligament in his right knee.Brown was 
injured in Sunday's 2-0 loss to Portland in Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown, a junior defender from Diamond Bar, has started 45 games for the Titans 
in three seasons and helped lead Fullerton to a 16-7 record and the semifinals 
of the NCAA playoffs last season. Coach Al Mistri called Brown's injury "a 
devastating loss." 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton is 6-3-1 this year and 1-0 in Mountain Pacific Sports Federation 
play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
