<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: BEVERLY HILLS; CHICAGO 
MAN FOUND SHOT TO DEATH IN ALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities on Monday identified a 39-year-old Chicago man found shot to death 
in a Beverly Hills' alley early Sunday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 Beverly Hills police identified the victim as Jon Simmons, who had been 
vacationing in Los Angeles with his brother.Simmons had gone out in West 
Hollywood Saturday evening, and when he failed to return the next day, his 
brother filed a missing persons report with the Los Angeles Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 A West Hollywood resident out for a walk came across the body at 7:20 a.m. The 
unidentified woman flagged down West Hollywood Councilman Paul Koretz, who was 
walking his dog, and he called police with his cellular telephone. 
</P>
<P>
 The man appeared to have been shot in the forehead, Koretz said. The burned 
hulk of Simmons' rental car was found in the San Gabriel Valley on Sunday 
morning. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the second murder in the past month in Beverly Hills, which averages 
one or two homicides a year. On Sept. 6, a Brinks armored car guard was killed 
as he was delivering money to a bank. 
</P>
