<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: PASADENA; BENEFITS OF 
WORLD CUP TO CITY TOTAL $4 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pasadena took in $2 million for its general fund and received about $2 million 
in improvements to the Rose Bowl last summer by hosting eight World Cup games, 
including the final, officials said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials had projected that extra security costs would require as much 
as $400,000 of the $2 million the city was due to receive for use of the Rose 
Bowl from World Cup USA.But unexpectedly light security demands during the 
nearly trouble-free tournament meant the city did not have to dip into the $2 
million, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 World Cup also paid for stadium improvements, including widening the Rose 
Bowl's field and building a handicapped seating area, as part of its contract 
with the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena officials have earmarked $1 million of the money for more police 
officers and anti-gang and recreation programs, and are placing the rest in 
reserve. 
</P>
