<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: TRIO-TECH REPORTS BOOST IN 4TH-QUARTER EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trio-Tech International, a San Fernando-based producer of semiconductor 
testing equipment, reported earnings of $489,000 for its fiscal fourth quarter 
that ended June 24. In the same quarter a year ago, the company posted a loss 
of $6,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Revenue in the latest quarter was $4.33 million, compared with year-earlier 
revenue of $3.62 million. For the year that ended June 24, Trio-Tech reported 
$2.04 million in income on revenue of $15.2 million, compared with year-earlier 
income of $103,000 on $15.7 million in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Trio-Tech attributed the improved results to streamlined operations, including 
trimming of the company's U. S. work force from 45 employees to 30. Trio-Tech 
has 587 employees worldwide, with operations in Europe and Asia. 
</P>
<P>
 The company, which manufactures equipment used to test the quality and 
reliability of semiconductors, also announced that it will complete a 1-for-4 
reverse stock split Oct 13. After the reverse split, the number of outstanding 
common shares will be reduced from 4.61 million to about 1.15 million.TRIO TECH 
INTERNATIONAL  
</P>
</TEXT>
