<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: HARMONY HOLDINGS REPORTS 4TH QUARTER TURNAROUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Harmony Holdings Inc., a Burbank producer of television commercials and 
videos, said its profit in the fiscal fourth quarter that ended June 30 was 
$292,000, compared to a loss of $1.7 million in the fourth quarter last 
year.The turnaround was on revenue of $9.7 million, up 33% from $7.3 million 
the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 For the fiscal year, Harmony Holdings narrowed its loss to $1.57 million, from 
$3.21 million last year. Revenues for the year grew 68% to $41.7 million from 
$24.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the results for the year to increased business at all 
of its four operating subsidiaries, and to internal restructuring which has cut 
overhead costs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
