<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SENIORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Achievements, activities 
</P>
<P>
 SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO 
</P>
<P>
 Join the Lunch Bunch -- or Get It Delivered 
</P>
<P>
 San Juan Capistrano Senior Program hosts noontime meals for older adults and 
delivers meals to homebound seniors. The meals are served daily at the San Juan 
Capistrano Senior Nutrition Center, 31421 La Matanza St. A $1.75 donation is 
requested. For reservations, call (714) 493-5921. 
</P>
<P>
 Home-delivered meals are intended for seniors who are unable to shop and cook 
for themselves. The meals are delivered between 10 a.m. and 1 p.m. For 
information or to volunteer as a driver, call (714) 493-5921. GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
<P>
 Going for the Gold at the Senior Games 
</P>
<P>
 No one is ever too old to play. 
</P>
<P>
 That's the concept behind the fifth annual Senior Games, which is expected to 
attract hundreds of participants. 
</P>
<P>
 The Friday and Saturday event will be at the H. Louis Lake Senior Citizens 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants will compete in billiards, Frisbee, shuffleboard, a half-mile 
walk, checkers, golf putting, horseshoe throwing and table tennis. Gold, silver 
and bronze medals will be awarded in each event. 
</P>
<P>
 The games are open to anyone 50 or older. The registration fee is $10. Each 
participant will receive a T-shirt and prize bag and join in a picnic with 
entertainment Saturday. PLACENTIA 
</P>
<P>
 Learn the Crafts of Painting, Carving 
</P>
<P>
 The Placentia Senior Center is looking for seniors to join its arts and 
handwork classes. 
</P>
<P>
 A new oil painting class will be forming this month for novices and those who 
just want to brush up. Dates and times will depend on response. 
</P>
<P>
 Seniors can enjoy a woodworking class under the instruction of master 
craftsmen who will demonstrate relief carving, carving in the round, swill chip 
carving, marquetry and other techniques. A $1 donation is requested for the 
woodworking class Tuesday from 7 to 9 p.m. at the center, 143 S. Bradford Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call (714) 993-6084. IRVINE 
</P>
<P>
 Assistance Programs Offered Monthly 
</P>
<P>
 Monthly programs at the Lakeview Senior Center in Irvine include: 
</P>
<P>
 Legal aid: 9:30 to 11:30 a.m. on the first Tuesday of each month. 
</P>
<P>
 Financial planning: 9 a.m. to noon on the second Thursday of each month. 
</P>
<P>
 Medicare counseling: 9 a.m. to noon on the second Tuesday and the fourth 
Monday of each month. 
</P>
<P>
 Blood pressure check: Noon to 1 p.m. on the second Thursday of each month. 
</P>
<P>
 For information about these and other assistance programs, call the Outreach 
Office at (714) 724-6808. 
</P>
