<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: VILLA PARK; CITIES TO SHARE COST OF REPAIRING TAFT AVENUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Taft Avenue divides Villa Park and Orange, so the two cities are dividing the 
cost of repairing the avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The Villa Park City Council unanimously voted last week for a joint agreement 
with Orange that calls for maintenance work on Taft Avenue from Sycamore Street 
to Loma Street.The maintenance includes street sealing and pavement 
rehabilitation. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange's share of the work is estimated to cost $21,402, and Villa Park's 
portion is estimated at $25,676. A contract will be awarded to the low bidder. 
</P>
<P>
 In a memo to the Villa Park council, City Engineer Jeff Thompson noted that 
Taft Avenue is a boundary for the two cities. "Due to the extensive work 
involved for the rehabilitation of Taft Avenue, the cities have mutually agreed 
to financially participate in this common project," Thompson said. 
</P>
<P>
 The joint agreement between the cities calls for the construction contract to 
be awarded by next February. BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
