<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; APPLICATIONS OPEN FOR IMAGINATION FEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Applications are available for Orange County-based artists and organizations 
seeking to participate in the 1995 Imagination Celebration of Orange County. 
The deadline is Oct. 28. 
</P>
<P>
 Marking its 10th anniversary next April, the Imagination Celebration is an 
annual festival of the arts for children, teen-agers and their families 
presented by the Orange County Performing Arts Center and the Orange County 
Department of Education. 
</P>
<P>
 The celebration annually draws 170,000 people to an array of workshops, 
performances, hands-on events and exhibits at various sites. 
</P>
<P>
 The festival will be presented at more than 30 sites around the county. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year's event included a street festival at Cal State Fullerton and 
musical performances by teens in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 To receive an application, call (714) 556-2122, Ext. 236. 
</P>
</TEXT>
