<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: DANA POINT; HARBOR BUSINESSES PLAN BIRTHDAY PARTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The price tag of meals and goods will be rolled back to 1971 levels as part of 
the Dana Point Harbor's 23rd birthday celebration this week. 
</P>
<P>
 Parking will be free in the harbor through Sunday.In addition, the Dana Point 
Harbor Assn. will sponsor several nautical exhibits, art shows, music and trip 
giveaways during the week. 
</P>
<P>
 Next Saturday, a line of custom made boats called the Water Angelman Wooden 
Boat Display will be shown at the Dana Wharf. The exhibit honors Hugh Angelman, 
a Southern California boat designer who began building yachts in the 1920s. 
</P>
<P>
 Members of the Niguel Art Assn. will show their work next weekend along the 
harbor walkway between Harpoon Henry's Restaurant and Dana Wharf. Clowns, music 
and other entertainment will also highlight the weekend near the Dana Wharf. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call (714) 496-1094.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
