<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The orange groves that once blanketed the county are quickly disappearing. 
</P>
<P>
 But the dried-bean industry is growing into one of the county's top producers. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the county agricultural report, dried beans are in big demand. 
The lima bean makes up the greatest proportion of the county's dried-bean crop. 
Today 
</P>
<P>
 Teen-agers interested in a career in the medical and health-care fields can 
attend an orientation workshop at Garden Grove Hospital and Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The hospital sponsors a medical explorer program for teens that is sanctioned 
by the Boy Scouts of America. Explorers can observe medical procedures and work 
in the emergency room. 
</P>
<P>
 The orientation begins at 7 p.m. at 1201 Garden Grove Blvd. Information: (714) 
741-2790. Tons of beans produced: 1993: 1,253 
</P>
