<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; HISTORIC TOWN CENTER DESIGNS TO BE 
SHOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City officials this week will unveil five design alternatives for a project 
envisioned as the centerpiece of downtown redevelopment. 
</P>
<P>
 A workshop at 7 p.m. Thursday will be repeated Friday.Both meetings are at 
City Hall, 32400 Paseo Adelanto. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents are invited to attend and comment on the five alternatives by 
filling out cards that will be available. Questions may also be asked of the 
city's planning staff. 
</P>
<P>
 The Historic Town Center has long been proposed for a six-acre parcel of 
city-owned land that straddles El Camino Real, south of Ortega Highway. 
</P>
<P>
 A plan for a 125-room hotel and large retail complex was scuttled in the late 
1980s after opposition from preservationists. 
</P>
<P>
 Since then, city officials have said they wanted residents to take a more 
active part in the project's planning. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
