<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOMINEES FOR SCHOOL DISTRICT HALL OF FAME BEING SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 So it's not Cooperstown. The Placentia-Yorba Linda Unified School District 
Hall of Fame still boasts some heavy hitters, including state Sen. John R. 
Lewis (R-Orange) and Olympic champion swimmer Janet Evans. 
</P>
<P>
 Now the district is looking for other graduates with gold medal qualifications 
to be inducted into the hall this school year. Candidates being sought are 
graduates of El Dorado, Valencia, Esperanza or El Camino Real high schools who 
have become successful in their chosen fields and are contributing members of 
society. 
</P>
<P>
 Candidates must also demonstrate high personal and professional standards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Hall of Fame was begun in January, 1992, to highlight the achievements of 
local students. In addition to Evans and Lewis, inductees include Elisa Bell, a 
screenwriter who graduated from Esperanza, and Rick Aguirre, an attorney and 
Valencia graduate. 
</P>
<P>
 Nominations will be accepted from teachers, district employees and community 
members through Oct. 21. The 1994-95 school year's inductees will be announced 
next spring.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the district office at (714) 996-2550. 
</P>
</TEXT>
