<P>
O.C. NEWSMAKERS: IRVINE SENSORS NAMES LIAN AS CEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kenneth T. Lian has been appointed chief executive of Irvine Sensors Corp., 
succeeding Chairman James Alexiou, who has formed an office of the chairman. 
Lian also joins the board of directors, filling a vacant slot.Lian is president 
and chief operating officer of the Costa Mesa computer electronics and infrared 
devices company. He joined Irvine Sensors as director of engineering and 
manufacturing in 1981 after being a product line manager at a Hughes Aircraft 
Co. subsidiary. He became Irvine Sensors' chief operating officer in 1986 and 
president in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, John J. Stuart Jr., chief financial officer and treasurer, has 
been appointed an advisory member of the board. Stuart joined Irvine Sensors in 
1983 as its manager of special projects and communications after having been 
president of The Business Group, a consulting company. He became Irvine 
Sensors' chief financial officer and treasurer in 1985. 
</P>
