<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RESTAURANTS AND RETAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Splitting Difference With Taxman: Del Taco Inc. in Orange has reached 
agreement with Orange County on a tax dispute, according to County Counsel 
Terry C. Andrus. 
</P>
<P>
 The tax dispute dates back to early 1993 when Del Taco voluntarily entered 
Chapter 11 proceedings in U.S. Bankruptcy Court in Santa Ana. Various tax 
claims were made and resolved last year, but late in 1993, the company and the 
county disagreed over $134,135.07 in taxes that the county claimed it was due. 
