<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOWNTIME: BODY WATCH; AN ELECTRIFYING DATE WITH THE PHANTOM SOOTHES THE SOUL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Home alone. The car pool has come and gone and blessed silence descends. It is 
time to escape into the music.I make my choice, and from the stereo the 
electrifying sounds of "The Phantom of the Opera" blaze out. Depending on my 
mood, I will become either the tremulous, haunted Christine or the elegant, 
sensuous, tortured Phantom. Today I am the Phantom. "Down once more to the 
dungeon of my black despair" as I clean up the breakfast dishes, swirling my 
black, silken cape around me. The haunting music fills my soul. I become one 
with this poor hunted creature. All too soon the van returns and regurgitates 
my children, and I must leave my dark lair and return to the daylight. 
</P>
<P>
 -- ADRIANNE C. ROSS, Newport Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
