<HEADLINE>
<P>
CELEBRATING 'THE SHVITZ' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN THOMAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Sunset 5 continues its Cinema Judaica series Wednesday with a one-week run 
of Jonathan Berman's warm, infectious 50-minute "The Shvitz," a celebration of 
the fast-vanishing communal pleasure of shvitzing (sweating) and schmoozing in 
Russian-Jewish-style steam baths, and Constance Marks' rueful, wryly amusing 
25-minute "Let's Fall in Love: A Singles Weekend at the Concord" (the famous 
Catskills resort hotel).  
</P>
<P>
 Also opening Friday at the Sunset 5 for a one-week run is Martin L. Aguilar's 
"Moondance," which begins promisingly as two couples (Joris Stuyck and Patti 
Tippo, Lisa Moncure and Steve Ruggles) in their 30s spend an increasingly edgy 
weekend in a mountain cabin but takes a nose-dive into awkward fantasy. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 848-3500. KEVIN THOMAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
