<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Menendez case -- In a Sept. 13 story about a dispute among jurors in the 
Menendez brothers murder trial, The Times reported one juror's statement that 
Judith Zamos, an alternate on the Lyle Menendez jury, had "called in and 
complained" during the trial about a television interview related to the case. 
In fact, the interview was broadcast after Zamos had ended her jury service, so 
she did not violate instructions that jurors avoid news reports on their case 
while serving on a panel. 
</P>
